# VPS Deployment Rules

## Deploy flow (fast path — always use this)

1. Build portals locally: `./scripts/build-portals.sh` → `deploy/dist/`
2. Upload changed files to VPS via `scp -i ~/.ssh/wakilfy_ed25519 ... root@165.22.124.111:...`
   (project lives at `/var/www/vodacom-caller-tunes`). The "Vodacom VPS" MCP server
   can also run remote commands.
3. On VPS: `docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.fast.yml --env-file .env.production build <service> && ... up -d <service> --force-recreate`
4. Verify externally: `curl -sk https://165.22.124.111/api/v1/tunes/customer/packages`

## Hard rules

- NEVER run `docker-compose.prod.yml` (the old file that builds portals on the VPS) —
  the 2GB VPS cannot handle parallel yarn builds. Use `docker-compose.prod.fast.yml`
  with pre-built `deploy/dist/` only.
- Laravel production env lives in `/var/www/vodacom-caller-tunes/.env.production`
  (APP_ENV=production makes Laravel prefer it). Adding env vars to `.env` only
  will silently do nothing in production.
- API container mounts the repo (`.:/var/www/html`); PHP code changes on the VPS
  apply after `docker restart vodacom-api` (composer runs in entrypoint).
- nginx config: `docker/nginx/nginx.conf` — subdomain vhosts on 443
  (admin/agent/referrals.biztune.co.tz), customer is `default_server`,
  `/api/` proxies to the api container. Rebuilding `web` re-copies dist + config.
- Self-signed certs are generated by `docker/nginx/entrypoint.sh`; Let's Encrypt
  via `scripts/setup-domain-ssl.sh` when needed.

## After every deploy

- `docker ps` — all 3 containers Up
- Check `docker logs vodacom-api --tail 20` for boot errors
- Curl-test: customer page (443), one API endpoint, and each subdomain
